# Functions and Injectivity
# Demonstrates: function signatures, Dom, injection concept.

Let S, T denote classes.
Let f denote a function.

Let x \in S stand for x is an element of S.

Definition Injective. f is injective iff for all elements x, y of Dom(f)
if f(x) = f(y) then x = y.

Definition Surjective. f surjects onto T iff for every element y of T
there exists an element x of Dom(f) such that f(x) = y.

# Simple test of the definitions.

Lemma. If f is injective and f is injective then f is injective.
